The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Monday, December 26, 2005 

 Leap second

 Washington, Dec. 24 (Reuters): Get ready for a minute with 61 seconds. Scientists are delaying the start of 2006 by the first leap second in seven years, a timing tweak meant to make up for changes in the Earths rotation.

 The adjustment will be carried out by sticking an extra second into atomic clocks worldwide at the stroke of midnight Coordinated Universal Time, the widely adopted international standard, the US National Insti-tute of Standards and Technology said.

 Enjoy New Years Eve a second longer, the institute said.

